r a BC-JAILERS-SLAIN-2NDTAKE     06-23 0313
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JAILERS-SLAIN-2NDTAKE-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
 c. 2000 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   HUNTSVILLE, Mo. _ information on Bulington.
The jail
</P>
<P>
   The shootings shocked the close-knit town of Huntsville.
</P>
<P>
   But local authorities have long complained about the jail, which
is housed in a two-story red brick building near two churches and
some houses.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is not a secure prison,'' Gordy said.
</P>
<P>
   Ancell went further.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think `security' is the wrong word,'' Ancell said. ``It's
just inadequate. That...old jail was built in 1909.''
</P>
<P>
   Several referendums on more money for law enforcement have been
rejected in recent years, including one last year that would have
financed a new jail, Gordy said.
</P>
<P>
   ``People want law enforcement, but they don't want to pay for
it,'' said a frustrated and distraught Ancell.
</P>
<P>
   Egley himself, in his role as city councilman, had lobbied for a
new jail.
</P>
<P>
   ``There always seems to be something wrong, and there's just too
many opportunities for something negative to happen,'' Egley told
the Moberly Monitor-Index last October.
</P>
<P>
   The 36 inmates in the jail Thursday morning have been moved to
other facilities.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm going to try to make (county officials) believe we have to
do some work on it'' before reopening the jail, Ancell said.
</P>
<P>
   A bulletproof glass barrier between the dispatch area and the
lobby would be the first order of business, he said. He also said
he'd like video cameras instead of just television monitors as
enhanced security.
</P>
<P>
   ``But it's not cheap,'' Ancell said. ``And the county's broke.''
</P>
<P>
   In the meantime, yellow crime tape encircles the jail. Its
front-yard flag flies at half-mast. And a rural county tries to
make sense of why two of its own were so violently lost.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's just hard to believe,'' Gordy said. ``We're all in a
state of shock.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-23-00 0110EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
