   BRYAN-CHAFIN _ Interview with Bryan Chafin, who plays Mel
Gibson's son in ``The Patriot,'' which opens Wednesday. (Garcia,
Austin American-Statesman). 20-25. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   TV-COLUMN _ PALM BEACH, Fla. _ ...and the winner for TV's ``Most
Underrated Drama'' goes to... ``Third Watch.'' (Thompson, Palm
Beach Post). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JANETLEIGH-PSYCHO _ Janet Leigh's biggest claim to fame cost
exactly one week of her life. That's how long it took Alfred
Hitchcock to film ``Psycho's'' memorable and horrific shower scene
_ a riveting montage (70 separate shots unfolding in roughly three
minutes). On Wednesday, Leigh brings ``Psycho'' to audiences for
free at the Fox summer film series. We talk to her about working
with Hitchcock, making the movie and its affect on her life.
(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30. FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-BROTHER _ Review of Scott Peterson's nonfiction ``Me
Against My Brother: At War in Somalia, Sudan and Rwanda.'' (Melvin,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35. FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-SKUBE _ Columnist Michael Skube on ``Portrait of an Artist
as an Old Man,'' the novel Joseph Heller finished just before he
died last year. (Skube, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. FOR
SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-READANDWHY _ Review of Harold Bloom's nonfiction ``How to
Read and Why.'' (Brock, Palm Beach Post). 24. FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   VIENNA - Apart from the traditional sites of this seat of
onetime Austrian royalty is a quite-uncommon house whose courtyard
faces the Danube Canal in a neighborhood where there are no
palaces. What makes the building appear unusual are the windows. No
two are alike. This is KunstHausWien, a privately-operated and
sponsored museum that pays homage to the art and architectural
representations of a most unusual man, Friedensreich Hundertwasser.
(Kleinberg, Cox News Service). MOVED Wednesday. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   DISCOVERY-COVE _ ORLANDO _ Experiencing/previewing Discovery
Cove, the new Sea World attraction where you can swim with dolphins
and come eye-to-eye with sharks and barracudas. It opens to the
public Saturday, July 1. (Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
WITH PHOTOS. FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ORLANDO-SIDE _ ORLANDO _ Checking out all this summer's new
attractions at Orlando's theme parks, including the interactive
``Men in Black Alien Attack'' at Universal Studios and Kraken
rollecoaster at Sea World. We grade each on the ``Wow'' factor.
(Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)WITH PHOTOS. FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   NAMIBIA _ ``I've always wanted to visit the motherland, and
three years ago I finally got the opportunity to go to Africa. I
enjoyed my experience so much that I have been back every year
since,'' Journal-Constitution photographer Keith Hadley says. This
year, Hadley visited Africa's gem, Namibia, ``where desert kisses
the sea.'' This hold-to-front story sets up a color photo page
inside of Hadley's pictures. ``Namibia's wide horizons and clear
unpolluted skies generate a sense of freedom,'' Hadley says. ``This
feeling of tranquility and stillness combines with a landscape that
is singular in its colors, full of contrasts of light and
shade...'' (Hadley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS. FOR
SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   NAMIBIA-SIDE _ Color photo essay of Namibia. (Hadley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS. FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-HANKIES _ Handkerchiefs are fashionable again, but these
days stylish women are wearing them on their back, not tucking them
into their sleeves. That's because hanky-inspired prints and
designs are cropping up everywhere, in halter tops, pants, blouses
and dresses.(AHill, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 4. WITH PHOTOS.
FOR SUNDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SELF-TANNER _ If you want to practice ``safe sun,'' make certain
your tan comes out of a bottle. Unlike the telltale orangy streaks
of self-tanners in the past, today's sunless products are
effective, fast and a smart way to achieve a natural-looking faux
glow. (MJohnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS. FOR
SUNDAY.
</P>
