<P>
   AIRBUS-SUPERJUMBO (Frankfurt, Germany) _ The four owners of
Airbus Industrie, the European consortium that rivals Boeing in the
commercial aircraft industry, formally announce they will proceed
with production of a 550-seat superjumbo plane, the A3XX. They also
restructure their consortium to form a single company and they
announce an initial public offering of EADS, which will own 80
percent of the new Airbus corporation. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
