shareholders of both companies vote on the proposal. By Saul
Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-SALES (Detroit) _ Automakers say that despite the recent
deep discounts, auto sales have not picked up in June from the
relatively subdued pace of May, providing further evidence for the
Federal Reserve that recent interest-rate increases may be slowing
the American economy. Demand is strongest for luxury cars and
luxury sport utility vehicles, but the mass market for more
affordable cars, minivans, sport utility vehicles and pickup trucks
has clearly softened. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-TELECOMS (Tokyo) _ NTT DoCoMo Inc., Japan's mighty
wireless communications company, is rumored to be on the verge of
spending 200 billion yen, or about $1.8 billion, to buy a 15
percent stake in the Canadian telecommunications company Telesystem
International Wireless Inc. as a means of entering the British
market. By Stephanie Strom.
