decision on whether to rehear the Elian Gonzalez case or not. If it
decides to reconsider the three-judge panel's ruling, it will
likely schedule another hearing. If it declines to reconsider it,
the case will then very likely be appealed to the U.S. Supreme
Court. (Rankin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
