   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ ATLANTA _ The inscription on the
Statue of Liberty that encourages the world's huddled masses to
become American citizens should be considered a historic curiosity,
not an immigration policy. (Rowland Nethaway is senior editor of
the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVEDLATHAM-COLUMN _ Jane made her
decision years ago and she was nothing more than a child, under 10
years old at the time. It wasn't something she wanted to do, but
ultimately either she would have made a decision or it would have
been made for her. Sometimes children have to make adult decisions.
Sometimes it is adults who force them to do so. (Latham, Marshall
News-Messenger) MOVEDMINTER-COLUMN _ Professional athletes usually
are big, strong and aggressive. That's why sportswriters, like
paratroopers and jet pilots, often get paid more than reporters who
