u k BC-EDITORIAL-BOYS0624-CO     06-23 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EDITORIAL-BOYS0624-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Can N.Y. rampage be explained?
 &HT;    By Maureen Downey
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ A lawyer for one of the men arrested in the Central
Park ``wilding case'' contends that it was ``a wet-T-shirt contest
that got out of control.''
</P>
<P>
   The 18 men arrested so far include a New York police officer's
younger brother, a minister's son and a father of two. Some had no
history of serious crime. It was hot, they said. They were
drinking. They just wanted to have fun.
</P>
<P>
   As many as 40 men participated in the roving assaults on 53
women and girls following the Puerto Rican Day Parade. Victims
ranged in age from 14 to 40. But if this was just another example
of ``boys will be boys,'' what's wrong with our boys?
</P>
<P>
   It would be convenient to blame the Sunday afternoon rampage on
an underclass of antisocial young thugs. So how do we account for
the hundreds of other men in Central Park who stood by as the
attacks took place, either gawking or capturing the degradation on
home video? None apparently bothered to use their ubiquitous cell
phones to call 911.
</P>
<P>
   Social commentators are lining up the usual suspects. It's the
misogynist nature of rap music. It's the blatant exploitation of
women in films. It's advertising that depicts women as sex objects.
It's a lying, skirt-chasing president in the White House. It's the
macho Latin culture.
</P>
<P>
   Then, there are the media, which replayed videos of half-naked
women fleeing the mob. If those images were supposed to convey the
horror of the attacks and thus deter others, they failed miserably.
</P>
<P>
   A few days after the tapes aired, Buffalo police arrested two
13-year-old boys who tossed water at two girls, chased them and,
after cornering one of them, ripped off her shirt and bra and
fondled her. The victims were 11.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-23-00 1629EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
