<P>
   AMAZON-STOCK (New York) _ Amazon.com stock Friday plunged 20
percent on the Nasdaq Stock Market. A Lehman Brothers fixed-income
analyst released a note describing the Seattle online book
retailer's ``extremely weak and deteriorating'' credit, and rumors
circulated that a Morgan Stanley Dean Witter Internet equities
analyst made bearish comments about the company, citing concerns
about flat second- and third-quarter 2000 revenue. The yellow flags
about Amazon.com, the biggest name among companies that sell to
consumers over the Internet, helped fuel jitters about the sector
overall. Web retailers are already battling fears of cash shortages
as interest rates rise. (Summary from wires) By Gretchen Morgenson.
