<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    UNITED PLANS CHALLENGE TO DELTA IN SOUTHEAST AFTER ITS MERGER
 &HT;    Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
 &HT;    By ROB O'DELL
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The head of United Airlines said Friday that if its
merger with US Airways goes through, the company plans to expand
its Charlotte, N.C., hub and challenge Delta Air Lines for
supremacy in the Southeast.
</P>
