<P>
   TIMEWARNER _ VIENNA, Va. and NEW YORK _ To the surprise of no
one, shareholders of Time Warner and America Online approved a
merger of the companies. The cakewalk is over. Now the companies
need to convince regulators in the U.S. and abroad that the deal
should be completed. Includes comments from analysts and
shareholders. (Geewax, Cox News Service in Virginia and Kempner in
New York, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22.
</P>
