<P>
   `PAPAL SIN' OFFERS HOPE FOR GAYS, CATHOLIC CHURCH. This week,
columnist Chuck Colbert reports on Gary Wills, a devout Catholic,
Pulitzer Prize-winning author and adjunct professor of history at
Northwestern University, whose just-published book, ``Papal Sin,''
offers a blistering attack on the papacy and its ``structures of
deceit.'' Colbert met Wills at a recent book reading at the Brattle
Theatre in Cambridge, Mass., and was impressed with what the writer
had to say. ``To be honest, I don't fully share (Wills')
optimism,'' Colbert writes. ``I don't, for example, hold much
hopein the near future for honesty and truth telling about
homosexuality and gay people in the public sphere _ at least from
priests and bishops, let alone officials in the Vatican. But his
