<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ ATLANTA _There tends to be a great deal of
romance surrounding any ancient craft such as woodworking or
pottery. This is all well and good, but a woodworker needs to
recognize it for what it is and not get too bound up in it. It's
usually at its strongest in the beginning stages of experience, and
when coupled with the natural urge to save a buck, it can lead to a
lot of misfortune. (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
