<P>
   Editors, features editors, Sunday editors:
</P>
<P>
   Starting July 23, the New York Times Sunday Book Review will
publish a children's book best-seller list in addition to its
regular adult lists.
</P>
<P>
   This new list will be added to the best-seller lists distributed
as part of The New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   To accommodate the new children's list, the two pages of the
Book Review that contain the adult hardcover and paperback best
seller lists have been redesigned. The ``Advice and How To''
hardcover list, usually at the bottom of the trade hardcover list,
is moving to the paperback best seller page. The new children's
book list will replace ``Advice and How To'' at the bottom of the
trade hardcover page.
</P>
<P>
   As this redesign is a work in progress, both for the Sunday Book
Review and the News Service, we will advise you later of its final
form.
</P>
<P>
   The new best-seller lists will also move in graphic form to NYT
graphics clients. For papers that are not clients of The News
Service, the new lists will be available from The N.Y. Times
Syndicate as a part of its book review package.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The New York Times News Service &LR;
</P>
