   RECORD-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ I was filled with emotions and memories as I stepped
off a bus one afternoon earlier this month and looked up at that
golden dome, considered by many to be the most famous of college
landmarks. It was appropriate that I was accompanied by my dear
friend, Don Hellinghausen of Midland. Don, then of Breckenridge,
and I first met more than 54 years ago as we ventured forth to
attend the University of Notre Dame. By PHIL RECORD. Story has
moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
