<P>
   EXECECUTION-REACT (New York) _ The United Nations joins the
European Union in denouncing the execution of Gary Graham as an
uncivilized act rejected by most of the world. By Joe Lauria. 700
words. (i and a coding)
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ELECTION (Shibukawa, Japan) _ Japan's economy is in a
stupor, the prime minister in the political doghouse and the young
generation in a hurry for change. Voters in most democratic
countries would send a clear message: ``Throw the bums out.'' But
not, it seems, in Japan. By Sharon Moshavi. 1150 words.
</P>
<P>
   ZIMBABWE-ELECTION (Harare, Zimbabwe) _ In the past decade, as
African countries have faced pressure from Western donors to allow
freely contested elections, fledgling opposition parties have had
little success surviving defeat at the ballot box. But Zimbabwe
appears set to break the mold. By Kurt Shillinger. 750 words.
</P>
