attractions at Orlando's theme parks, including the interactive
``Men in Black Alien Attack'' at Universal Studios and Kraken
rollecoaster at Sea World. We grade each on the ``Wow'' factor.
(Hamilton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   NAMIBIA _ ``I've always wanted to visit the motherland, and
three years ago I finally got the opportunity to go to Africa. I
enjoyed my experience so much that I have been back every year
since,'' Journal-Constitution photographer Keith Hadley says. This
year, Hadley visited Africa's gem, Namibia, ``where desert kisses
the sea.'' This hold-to-front story sets up a color photo page
inside of Hadley's pictures. ``Namibia's wide horizons and clear
unpolluted skies generate a sense of freedom,'' Hadley says. ``This
feeling of tranquility and stillness combines with a landscape that
is singular in its colors, full of contrasts of light and
shade...'' (Hadley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   NAMIBIA-SIDE _ Color photo essay of Namibia. (Hadley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS.
