<HEADLINE>
TIPS FOR HOME OFFICES
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: First of 2 sidebars; goes with Home Office main) 
By ANGELA LEMIRE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   When setting up a home-based business, be sure to meet all legal
requirements:
</P>
<P>
   1. Check with your local city clerk and zoning, building and
safety departments for complete listings of home occupation
guidelines and restrictions.
</P>
<P>
   The City of Los Angeles zoning ordinance, for example, prohibits
certain occupations in the home, such as adult entertainment,
animal training, body piercing, massage therapy and others. The
city also prohibits home offices from displaying business signs,
receiving more than one client per hour, creating a public
nuisance, having more than one employee and operating before 8 a.m.
and after 8 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   2. Obtain a business license.
</P>
<P>
   Most cities, including the City of Los Angeles, require
residents to obtain a business license to conduct specific
occupations. License fees cost $25 for initial registration and $25
annually.
</P>
<P>
   3. If necessary, obtain a home occupancy permit.
</P>
<P>
   Some cities require one. The City of Los Angeles currently does
not.
</P>
<P>
   4. Notify your insurance agent.
</P>
<P>
   Make sure your home office has property insurance coverage, plus
any other coverage required for businesses, especially if you are
employing anyone in your office or receiving clients. Policies for
residential homes vary and might not automatically cover home-based
business offices.
</P>
<P>
   5. Consult an accountant or call the Internal Revenue Service to
find out special tax considerations and laws that pertain to
home-based businesses, as well as home offices used for
telecommuting.
</P>
<P>
   6. Before performing any construction or renovations _ either
interior or exterior _ obtain a building permit from your city of
residence. &QL; 
---Sources City of Los Angeles, Economic Alliance of San Fernando
Valley &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
