<SLUG> BC-AZR-BUDGET-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, June 24. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
WIGS (Phoenix) - The mother and sister of a jail breaker were
forced to put on wigs, fakenoses, glasses and excessive makeup in
the Maricopa County Sheriff's Office as part of an investigation
into how convicted double-murder Tasha Wolf escaped. But the
court-ordered dress up session earlier this week for Betsy Brewer,
the mom, and the sister didn't produce any damaging evidence
against them, said Richard Gierloff, the family's attorney.
Gierloff declined to identify the sister. By CRAIG HARRIS. Story
will move in the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
USWEST (Phoenix) - Arizona's US West customers soon will be writing
out their monthly checks to a different phone company. The state
Corporation Commission gave its unanimous blessing Friday to the
marriage of US West and Qwest Communiciations International, the
final hurdle to completing the $52 billion merger. By HAL MATTERN.
Story will move in the `F` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
ME-MOVIE (Undated) - Near the end of `Me, Myself &AMP; Irene,` Jim
Carrey beats himself up. Heaven knows he deserves it. It's fair
punishment for starring in this moronic farce, which lurches from
tragically unfunny to pointlessly raunchy with the grace of a
drunken wildebeest. By BILL MULLER. Story moved in the `E''
category.
</P>
<P>
   CHICKEN-MOVIE (Undated) - One can only imagine the pitch meeting
for `Chicken Run`: `Hey, let's remake The Great Escape, only with
chickens.''Funny thing is, it works. The creators of BBC animation
favorites `Wallace &AMP; Gromit` offer up a delightful tale about a
group of chickens trying to escape from a bleak egg farm before
their evil human owners turn them into potpies. By BILL MULLER.
Story moved in the `E'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
