   GORE-FUNDRAISING (Washington) _ In a caustic exchange with a
senior Justice Department prosecutor last April, Vice President Al
Gore denied that he had been told by aides that a 1996 luncheon at
a Buddhist temple was a fund-raising event, according to a
transcript of the interview that the Vice President lawyers
released. By David Johnston and Don Van Natta Jr. (We plan to move
the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 2,200 words.
</P>
