   With 3-column photo, NYT2.
</P>
<P>
   Inside: GORE-ASSESS (Undated) _ News analysis: For the last
year, Vice President Al Gore has been working furiously to separate
himself from the scandals of the Clinton administration, an
administration that has been accused repeatedly of not telling the
truth. Now, four and a half months before the presidential
election, that same charge has landed squarely on the vice
president. By Katharine Q. Seelye. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET
in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   POST-HIGH-SCHOOL (Undated) _ Post-grad programs have been around
for decades, but over the last five years, with the competition for
entry into top-tier colleges growing more fevered than ever, the
post-graduate programs have begun drawing far more applicants and
from a wider pool that for the first time, includes a substantial
number of girls, and boys, less interested in athletics than drama,
music or a more impressive academic profile. And public school
officials have even begun to talk of a fifth year of high school.
By Tamar Lewin. (The story has moved in ``a'' news file.) 1,700
words.
</P>
