<P>
   CUBAN-BOY (Miami) _ A federal appeals court in Atlanta has
refused to reconsider the case of Elian Gonzalez, leaving the
Supreme Court as a last hope for the Miami relatives who want to
prevent his return to Cuba. By Rick Bragg. (An early version has
moved and will be updated.)
</P>
<P>
   CLEAN-AIR-RULES (Washington) _ A federal appeals court has
upheld a new air-pollution program meant to drastically reduce smog
that flows from the Middle West to the East, an endeavor that
federal officials estimate will cost $1.7 billion annually over 15
years but make up for it in lower medical costs and better public
health. By David Stout. (Scheduled to move by 8:45 p.m. ET in ``w''
news file.) 800 words.
