<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Atlanta Ballet, Indigo Girls to collaborate
 &HT;    By Wendell Brock
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Atlanta Ballet has engaged the Indigo Girls to
collaborate next season on a world premiere in which the
Atlanta-based pop singers will perform original music with the
company at the Fox Theatre.
</P>
<P>
   The ballet has not chosen a choreographer for the March 15-18
production, but artistic director John McFall says he wants to
bring in a woman choreographer to work with the perennially popular
lesbian duo of Emily Saliers and Amy Ray. ``I think there's a
simpatico there that you can only achieve by taking that route,''
McFall said Friday, in announcing the lineup for the 2000-2001
season.
</P>
<P>
   The Indigo Girls are in the midst of a national tour and could
not be reached for comment, but McFall said they would write at
least two new songs for the 25-minute work. On the same ticket will
be a world premiere by Laura Dean (``Earth'') and a company
premiere by Australian choreographer Stanton Welch (``Garden of
Mirth'').
</P>
<P>
   At a time when dance can be a hard sell, the Indigo Girls
collaboration should broaden the ballet's audience and boost its
box office.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
