NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, JUNE 24
</HEADLINE>
  ( Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-NY-EGAN-INSTALL-NYT (moved on Monday, June 19)  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 19,
about the installation of Archbishop Edward M. Egan of New York
misstated the given name of a spokeswoman for Hillary Rodham
Clinton, who explained that Mrs. Clinton had attended the ceremony
in her role as first lady, not as a Senate candidate. She is Lissa
Muscatine, not Ilissa.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ALLIANCE-MARKETPLACE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, June 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 20,
about the acquisition of Sanford C. Bernstein &AMP; Company by Alliance
Capital Management misstated the amount paid in another recent deal
between money management firms. Last week, Nvest agreed to be
acquired by CDC Asset Management &UR; coei &LR;  for $1.9 billion, not $700
million.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-BOOK-RECAST-NYT (moved on Monday, June 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 12,
about the book ``Nuestros Cuerpos, Nuestras Vidas,'' a Latina
version of the women's health book ``Our Bodies, Ourselves''
imprecisely characterized comments by Dr. Jane L. Delgado,
president and chief executive of the National Alliance for Hispanic
Health, a nonprofit network of Hispanic health providers. Dr.
Delgado said that in saying that a book's acceptance should be
helped by paying respect to the cultural cornerstones of faith and
family, she was referring to her own book, ``Salud!''a guide to
health for Hispanic women, not to ``Nuestros Cuerpos, Nuestras
Vidas.''
</P>
<P>
   BC-ART-NOTES-NYT (moved on Thursday, June 22)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, June 22,
about an art exhibition scheduled to open Jan. 1 at the San
Francisco Museum of Art, omitted a numeral from the title of the
exhibition. It is ``01.01.01: Art in Technological Times,'' not
``01.0.01.''
</P>
