   (NYT16) MEXICO CITY -- June 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. JUNE 25 --
MEXICO-PRI-COX -- For 71 years the Institutional Revolutionary
Party, also known as the PRI, has controlled Mexico's presidency
and most other political offices throughout the country. The party
rose from the ashes of the 1910 Mexican Revolution and managed to
turn a feudal country into an industrial, oil-producing nation. The
PRI hopes that on July 2, supporters of their policies turn out to
vote and help the party hang on to the presidency. Victor
Montelongo is a farmers' organizer for the PRI. (Luis J. Jimnez/Cox
News Service Photo)
</P>
