   (NYT11) DAMASCUS, Syria -- June 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR MON. JUNE
26 -- SYRIA-INTERNET-COX -- Syria is famous for restrictive,
socialist-style planning. While other countries thrive off the
freedom and spontaneity of Internet use, Syria dribbles out
licenses to use it. Zoni Internet Service is one of at least three
non-government Internet shops opening in the last nine months in
Damascus. Imad Sakker works at Zoni, where web surfing is
relatively uncensored. (Larry Kaplow/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
