<P>
   (NYT6) GRANITE BAY, Calif. -- June 23, 2000 -- POST-HIGH-SCHOOL
-- Post-high school programs have been around for decades at dozens
of New England boarding schools like Phillips Exeter, Hotchkiss and
Deerfield, mostly for male athletes who have graduated from public
high schools and want an extra year to get stronger and bolster
less-than-stellar academic records. But over the last five years,
they have been drawing far more applicants, including, for the
first time, a substantial number of girls, and boys who are more
interested in drama or music than in athletics. Jeff Blumenfeld
hugs a classmate after his commencement ceremony at Granite Bay
High School in Granite Bay California. (Don Preisler/The New York
Times)
</P>
