<P>
   (NYT1) UNDATED -- June 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JUNE 25 --
LEVI-STRAUSS -- With sales falling and profits scarce, Robert Haas,
the beleaguered chairman of Levi Strauss &AMP; Co., struggles to
preserve Levi Strauss as a clothing maker with a conscience. Levi's
announced results last week suggest only that the company has
slowed its decline. It therefore remains unclear whether the
company can endure with its legacy of social responsibility intact.
Hass in a 1996 file photo. (Levi Strauss &AMP; Co./The New York Times)
