landscape, a store's dressing room is part dream chamber, part
orgone box and a retail no man's land. Often cramped, creepy and
hard to locate, it is sometimes locked tighter than an ICBM
installation and sometimes so public it could be the stage set for
an ``Oh! Calcutta!'' revival. The dressing room at Loehman's.
(Marilynn K. Yee/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) WASHINGTON -- June 23, 2000 -- GORE-RENO -- Attorney
General Janet Reno said Friday she would resist any pressure to
rush to determine whether Vice President Al Gore told investigators
the truth about his role in 1996 fund-raising efforts. Reno heads
to her seat for a news conference, Friday. (Paul Hosefros/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) UNDATED -- June 23, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., JUNE 25 --
