   &UR; WESTERN CARMAKERS DISCOVER THAILAND &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THAILAND-AUTOMAKERS-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   AMATA CITY AND SAMRONG _ They are cheap, educated, friendly and
fastidious, and Ralph-Rainer Ohlsen loves them. He smiles benignly
at the women and men assembling BMWs in the light-flooded,
squeaky-clean factory in Thailand's Rayong province that he opened
last month. ``Those Thais even take their shoes off when they get
in the cars,'' he enthuses. ``It's great.'' Following Ford last
year and GM in April, BMW is the latest western carmaker to set up
shop in Thailand. &QL;
</P>
