<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KC </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TRADING TO START EARLY IN SHARES OF DIVIDED KC SOUTHERN
INDUSTRIES 
</HEADLINE>
 SOUTHERN-KAN   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 BY MARK DAVIS, KNIGHT RIDDER NEWSPAPERS   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Wall Street plans to start trading shares from next month's
breakup of Kansas City Southern Industries Inc. as early as Monday,
the financial services and transportation company said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Kansas City Southern plans to spin off its financial services
companies, including the Janus mutual fund family, on July 12. The
breakup will create a new company called Stilwell Financial and
leave Kansas City Southern with its railway.
</P>
<P>
   The company plans to distribute Stilwell shares to owners of
Kansas City Southern shares as of June 28.
</P>
<P>
   But three separate stocks are expected to begin trading next
week on the New York Stock Exchange, Kansas City Southern's
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
   One stock will represent ownership of the as yet unborn
Stilwell. The Stilwell shares will begin trading next week on a
``when-issued'' basis under the symbol SV.
</P>
<P>
   Another of the three stocks will represent ownership of the
continuing combined company that exists today. Those shares will
trade under the symbol KSU and will trade with ``due bill
attached,'' which entitles the owner to both the Stilwell shares
when they are spun off and shares of the remaining railway company.
</P>
<P>
   The third of the three stocks will represent ownership of the
soon-to-be-stand-alone railway company. These shares also will
trade on a ``when- issued'' basis, under the symbol KSU-WI.
</P>
<P>
   The railway shares will represent ownership after a planned
1-for-2 reverse stock split by the railway company. Investors will
end up with half the number of shares but with the same total value
because the new share price will double to reflect the reverse
split. The move will keep the share price above $5, the price
needed for investors to buy shares on credit.
</P>
<P>
   On July 13, when the breakup actually happens, regular trading
will begin in Stilwell shares and shares of the stand-alone railway
company. The railway company will be called Kansas City Southern
but will have new certificates and a new identification on Wall
Street.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
